### Composite Channel Credentials

```cpp
// Declared in: include/grpcpp/security/credentials.h

std::shared_ptr<ChannelCredentials> grpc::CompositeChannelCredentials(
    const std::shared_ptr<ChannelCredentials>& channel_creds,
    const std::shared_ptr<CallCredentials>&    call_creds);
```

Combines a `ChannelCredentials` (transport security) with a `CallCredentials`
(per-call token) into a single `ChannelCredentials` object. Every RPC on the
resulting channel automatically attaches the call credentials.

| Parameter | Type | Description |
|-----------|------|-------------|
| `channel_creds` | `std::shared_ptr<ChannelCredentials>` | Provides transport-layer security (e.g., `SslCredentials`). |
| `call_creds` | `std::shared_ptr<CallCredentials>` | Provides per-call authentication tokens (e.g., `AccessTokenCredentials`, `ServiceAccountJWTAccessCredentials`). |

**Example — SSL transport + OAuth2 access token:**

```cpp
auto channel_creds = grpc::SslCredentials(grpc::SslCredentialsOptions());
auto call_creds    = grpc::AccessTokenCredentials(oauth2_token);
auto composite     = grpc::CompositeChannelCredentials(channel_creds, call_creds);

auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel("api.example.com:443", composite);
```

**Example — SSL transport + service-account JWT:**

```cpp
auto channel_creds = grpc::SslCredentials(grpc::SslCredentialsOptions());
auto call_creds    = grpc::ServiceAccountJWTAccessCredentials(json_key_string);
auto composite     = grpc::CompositeChannelCredentials(channel_creds, call_creds);

auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel("api.example.com:443", composite);
```

