### Google Default Credentials

```cpp
std::shared_ptr<ChannelCredentials> grpc::GoogleDefaultCredentials();
```

> **Warning:** Use only when connecting to Google endpoints. Using these
> credentials with a non-Google service may allow that service to impersonate
> your client for Google API requests.

Builds credentials using [Application Default Credentials (ADC)](https://cloud.google.com/docs/authentication/application-default-credentials).
The credential source is resolved in this order:

1. `GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS` environment variable (service account JSON)
2. `gcloud auth application-default login` user credentials
3. Attached service account (when running on GCP)

**Example:**

```cpp
auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel(
    "pubsub.googleapis.com:443",
    grpc::GoogleDefaultCredentials());
```

