### Advanced TLS Credentials (experimental)

```cpp
// Declared in: include/grpcpp/security/credentials.h
namespace grpc::experimental {

std::shared_ptr<ChannelCredentials> TlsCredentials(
    const TlsChannelCredentialsOptions& options);

}  // namespace grpc::experimental
```

Provides fine-grained TLS control via `TlsChannelCredentialsOptions`
(declared in `include/grpcpp/security/tls_credentials_options.h`). Key
capabilities beyond `SslCredentials`:

- Dynamic certificate reloading via `CertificateProviderInterface`
- Custom post-handshake peer verification via `CertificateVerifier`
- CRL (Certificate Revocation List) enforcement via `CrlProvider`
- Configurable minimum/maximum TLS version (`grpc_tls_version`)

**Example — dynamic certificate reload:**

```cpp
#include <grpcpp/security/tls_credentials_options.h>
#include <grpcpp/security/tls_certificate_provider.h>

// Provider that watches files on disk and reloads on change.
auto provider = std::make_shared<grpc::experimental::FileWatcherCertificateProvider>(
    "client.key", "client.crt", "ca.pem",
    /*refresh_interval_sec=*/600);

grpc::experimental::TlsChannelCredentialsOptions tls_opts;
tls_opts.set_certificate_provider(provider);
tls_opts.watch_root_certs();
tls_opts.watch_identity_key_cert_pairs();

auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel(
    "api.example.com:443",
    grpc::experimental::TlsCredentials(tls_opts));
```

