### `CallCredentials` Factory Functions

`CallCredentials` objects are attached to a channel via
`CompositeChannelCredentials`, or applied per-call via
`ClientContext::set_credentials`.

| Factory | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `grpc::AccessTokenCredentials(token)` | Attaches a raw OAuth2 bearer token. |
| `grpc::ServiceAccountJWTAccessCredentials(json_key, lifetime_secs)` | Signs JWTs with a service-account private key. Default lifetime: 3600 s (`kMaxAuthTokenLifetimeSecs`). |
| `grpc::GoogleComputeEngineCredentials()` | Fetches tokens from the GCE metadata server. |
| `grpc::GoogleRefreshTokenCredentials(json_refresh_token)` | Exchanges a refresh token for access tokens. |
| `grpc::GoogleIAMCredentials(auth_token, authority_selector)` | Attaches Google IAM authorization metadata. |
| `grpc::MetadataCredentialsFromPlugin(plugin)` | Injects arbitrary metadata via a user-defined `MetadataCredentialsPlugin`. |
| `grpc::ExternalAccountCredentials(json_string, scopes)` | Workload identity federation credentials. |
| `grpc::CompositeCallCredentials(creds1, creds2)` | Combines two `CallCredentials` objects. |
| `grpc::experimental::StsCredentials(options)` | STS OAuth Token Exchange (IETF draft). |

