## `grpc::ChannelArguments`

```cpp
// Declared in: include/grpcpp/support/channel_arguments.h
namespace grpc {

class ChannelArguments {
 public:
  ChannelArguments();

  // gRPC-specific typed setters
  void SetSslTargetNameOverride(const std::string& name);
  void SetCompressionAlgorithm(grpc_compression_algorithm algorithm);
  void SetGrpclbFallbackTimeout(int fallback_timeout_ms);
  void SetSocketMutator(grpc_socket_mutator* mutator);
  void SetUserAgentPrefix(const std::string& user_agent_prefix);
  void SetResourceQuota(const grpc::ResourceQuota& resource_quota);
  void SetMaxReceiveMessageSize(int size);
  void SetMaxSendMessageSize(int size);
  void SetLoadBalancingPolicyName(const std::string& lb_policy_name);
  void SetServiceConfigJSON(const std::string& service_config_json);

  // Generic low-level setters (advanced use only)
  void SetInt(const std::string& key, int value);
  void SetString(const std::string& key, const std::string& value);
  void SetPointer(const std::string& key, void* value);
  void SetPointerWithVtable(const std::string& key, void* value,
                            const grpc_arg_pointer_vtable* vtable);
};

}  // namespace grpc
```

`ChannelArguments` is a value type (copyable and assignable). Construct one,
call the desired setters, then pass it to `CreateCustomChannel`.

### Typed Setter Reference

| Method | Underlying key | Description |
|--------|---------------|-------------|
| `SetMaxReceiveMessageSize(int bytes)` | `grpc.max_receive_message_length` | Maximum inbound message size in bytes. `-1` = unlimited. Default: 4 MiB. |
| `SetMaxSendMessageSize(int bytes)` | `grpc.max_send_message_length` | Maximum outbound message size in bytes. `-1` = unlimited. Default: unlimited. |
| `SetCompressionAlgorithm(algo)` | `grpc.default_compression_algorithm` | Default compression algorithm for all messages on the channel. |
| `SetLoadBalancingPolicyName(name)` | `grpc.lb_policy_name` | Override the load-balancing policy (e.g., `"round_robin"`, `"pick_first"`, `"grpclb"`). Ignored when the resolver returns balancer addresses. |
| `SetServiceConfigJSON(json)` | `grpc.service_config` | Inline service config in JSON. Ignored if the name resolver returns a service config. |
| `SetUserAgentPrefix(prefix)` | `grpc.primary_user_agent` | String prepended to the `user-agent` header on every request. |
| `SetResourceQuota(quota)` | `grpc.resource_quota` | Attach a `ResourceQuota` to cap memory usage across channels. |
| `SetSslTargetNameOverride(name)` | `grpc.ssl_target_name_override` | Override the hostname used for SSL certificate verification. **Testing only.** |
| `SetGrpclbFallbackTimeout(ms)` | `grpc.grpclb_fallback_timeout_ms` | Time (ms) to wait for a non-empty server list from the balancer before falling back to resolver addresses. |
| `SetSocketMutator(mutator)` | `grpc.socket_mutator` | Apply custom socket options (e.g., `SO_MARK`) via a `grpc_socket_mutator`. |

### Common Raw Keys (via `SetInt` / `SetString`)

These keys are defined in `include/grpc/impl/channel_arg_names.h` and are
passed through `SetInt` or `SetString` when no typed setter exists.

| Key constant | String value | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `GRPC_ARG_KEEPALIVE_TIME_MS` | `"grpc.keepalive_time_ms"` | int | Interval (ms) between keepalive pings. |
| `GRPC_ARG_KEEPALIVE_TIMEOUT_MS` | `"grpc.keepalive_timeout_ms"` | int | Time (ms) to wait for a keepalive ping ACK before closing the transport. |
| `GRPC_ARG_KEEPALIVE_PERMIT_WITHOUT_CALLS` | `"grpc.keepalive_permit_without_calls"` | int (0/1) | Allow keepalive pings when there are no active RPCs. |
| `GRPC_ARG_MIN_RECONNECT_BACKOFF_MS` | `"grpc.min_reconnect_backoff_ms"` | int | Minimum backoff (ms) between reconnection attempts. |
| `GRPC_ARG_MAX_RECONNECT_BACKOFF_MS` | `"grpc.max_reconnect_backoff_ms"` | int | Maximum backoff (ms) between reconnection attempts. |
| `GRPC_ARG_INITIAL_RECONNECT_BACKOFF_MS` | `"grpc.initial_reconnect_backoff_ms"` | int | Backoff (ms) for the first reconnection attempt. |
| `GRPC_ARG_CLIENT_IDLE_TIMEOUT_MS` | `"grpc.client_idle_timeout_ms"` | int | Time (ms) after the last RPC before the channel enters IDLE. Default: 30 min. |
| `GRPC_ARG_MAX_CONCURRENT_STREAMS` | `"grpc.max_concurrent_streams"` | int | Maximum concurrent HTTP/2 streams per connection. |
| `GRPC_ARG_HTTP2_MAX_FRAME_SIZE` | `"grpc.http2.max_frame_size"` | int | Maximum HTTP/2 frame size (bytes). Range: 16384–16777215. |
| `GRPC_ARG_HTTP2_WRITE_BUFFER_SIZE` | `"grpc.http2.write_buffer_size"` | int | Per-stream write buffer size (bytes) when `GRPC_WRITE_BUFFER_HINT` is set. |
| `GRPC_ARG_DEFAULT_AUTHORITY` | `"grpc.default_authority"` | string | Default `:authority` / `Host` header value. |
| `GRPC_ARG_MAX_METADATA_SIZE` | `"grpc.max_metadata_size"` | int | Soft limit (bytes) on total metadata per RPC batch. |
| `GRPC_ARG_ENABLE_CHANNELZ` | `"grpc.enable_channelz"` | int (0/1) | Enable/disable Channelz introspection. Default: enabled. |
| `GRPC_ARG_LB_POLICY_NAME` | `"grpc.lb_policy_name"` | string | Load-balancing policy name (same as `SetLoadBalancingPolicyName`). |

