## Stub Instantiation

Generated stubs are created from a channel using the static `NewStub` factory.
The stub holds a `shared_ptr` to the channel internally, so the channel remains
alive as long as the stub is alive.

```cpp
// Synchronous (blocking) stub
std::unique_ptr<ServiceName::Stub> stub =
    ServiceName::NewStub(channel);

// Asynchronous stub — same type, same factory
std::unique_ptr<ServiceName::Stub> async_stub =
    ServiceName::NewStub(channel);
// Use stub->async()->MethodName(...) for async RPCs.
```

Multiple stubs can share a single channel:

```cpp
auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel("backend:443", creds);

auto greeter_stub = helloworld::Greeter::NewStub(channel);
auto health_stub  = grpc::health::v1::Health::NewStub(channel);
```

