## Channel Connectivity States

A channel transitions through the following states (defined in
`grpc_connectivity_state`):

| State | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `GRPC_CHANNEL_IDLE` | No active RPCs; channel is not trying to connect. |
| `GRPC_CHANNEL_CONNECTING` | Actively trying to establish a connection. |
| `GRPC_CHANNEL_READY` | Connected and ready to send RPCs. |
| `GRPC_CHANNEL_TRANSIENT_FAILURE` | Transient failure; will retry with backoff. |
| `GRPC_CHANNEL_SHUTDOWN` | Channel has been shut down permanently. |

```cpp
// Query current state; pass true to trigger a connection attempt from IDLE.
grpc_connectivity_state state = channel->GetState(/*try_to_connect=*/true);
```

