## Error Handling: Lame Channels

When `CreateChannel` or `CreateCustomChannel` receives a null or invalid
`ChannelCredentials` pointer, it returns a **lame channel** rather than a null
pointer. Every RPC attempted on a lame channel fails immediately with
`grpc::StatusCode::UNKNOWN`. This design ensures that callers never need to
null-check the returned channel pointer.

```cpp
// Passing nullptr produces a lame channel — all RPCs will fail.
auto channel = grpc::CreateChannel("localhost:50051", nullptr);
auto stub    = helloworld::Greeter::NewStub(channel);

grpc::ClientContext ctx;
helloworld::HelloRequest req;
helloworld::HelloReply reply;
grpc::Status status = stub->SayHello(&ctx, req, &reply);
// status.ok() == false, status.error_code() == grpc::StatusCode::UNKNOWN
```

